# AGENTS.md — {{name}}

## Purpose
This project was forged by the **Foundry Software Factory**. It uses Next.js on Cloudflare Workers (OpenNext).

## Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router, React 19)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/postcss`, CSS-first config)
- **Lint/Format**: Biome
- **Testing**: Vitest
- **Deploy**: Cloudflare Workers via `@opennextjs/cloudflare`

## Tailwind v4 Setup
- No `tailwind.config.ts` — Tailwind v4 uses CSS-first config (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `src/app/globals.css`)
- PostCSS config in `postcss.config.mjs` uses `@tailwindcss/postcss`
- Note: `experimental.useLightningcss: true` in Next.js conflicts with Tailwind v4 — do not enable it

## Context
- **Project Name**: {{name}}
- **Standard**: Foundry Gold Standard (v1)
- **Infrastructure**: Managed via `fnd` (Foundry Commander)
- **Backend services**: Use `@saas-maker/sdk` when linking to the fleet API.

## Key commands
```bash
pnpm dev      # next dev
pnpm build    # next build
pnpm start    # next start
pnpm lint     # biome check .
pnpm test     # vitest run
```

## Standard Procedures for Agents

### 1. Code Changes
- Use `@` path alias for imports from `src/`.
- Keep Tailwind utilities as the default styling approach.
- Use Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed.

### 2. Maintenance
- Run `fnd audit` inside this directory to verify compliance.
- Run `fnd fleet upgrade` to refresh devDependencies.
